1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15.1-07 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the use of personal electronic devices during instructional time.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15.1-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Personal electronic devices - Prohibition during instructional time.
7 1. As used in this section:
8 a. "Instructional time" means the time from the start of the school day until dismissal
9 at the end of the school day on school premises, for which the signal may be the
10 ringing of a bell, including a structured or unstructured learning experience,
11 recess, a lunch period, and time in between classes. The term does not include
12 private student travel time to and from an area career and technology center or
13 other offsite learning experience or instructional time occurring in virtual
14 environments off school premises.
15 b. "Parent" means a parent or guardian of a student who is authorized to make
16 decisions regarding education for the student.
17 c. "Personal electronic communication device" means a portable electronic device
18 capable of communication by voice, text, or other data with one or more other
19 parties or devices, or capable of connection to a smartphone, the internet, or a
20 cellular or wireless fidelity network, including a smartphone, cell phone,
21 bluetooth-enabled device, tablet, smartwatch or other wearable device, and
22 gaming device. The term does not include:
