1 (1) School-owned devices provided to a student and school-approved devices
2 used by a student in accordance with this section.
3 (2) Portable devices that meet the definition of a medical device under the
4 federal Food, Drug and Cosmetic Act [21 U.S.C. 9 et seq.].
5 d. "School" means a public school providing prekindergarten, elementary, or
6 secondary education, including area career and technology centers. The term
7 does not include virtual schools, virtual instruction, the North Dakota center for
8 distance education, or education occurring in a home-school environment.
9 e. "School-related activity" means a school sanctioned activity, event, or function,
10 occurring outside of instructional time, at which students are under supervision of
11 the school, whether on or off school premises, including a bus ride, field trip,
12 sporting event, and school dance.
13 f. "Student" means an individual currently enrolled or registered at a school.
14 2. Each school district or applicable governing body shall adopt and implement a policy
15 for schools which:
16 a. Requires all personal electronic communication devices be silenced or turned off,
17 securely locked away, and inaccessible to students during instructional time;
18 b. Ensures students do not have access to personal electronic communication
19 devices, by requiring the devices to be locked or stowed away in a secure
20 lockable pouch, phone locker, pencil pouch, manila envelope, or other
21 inaccessible location;
22 c. Provides schools may limit or allow student access to personal electronic
23 communication devices outside of instructional time, during a school-related
24 activity;
25 d. Includes enforcement provisions to ensure strict compliance with the policy by
26 students and school employees; and
27 e. Provides a student may contact the student's parent or authorized caregiver
28 during the school day if needed by using a school telephone made available to
29 the student in a manner and location designated by the school.
30 3. Notwithstanding subsection 2, a school may not prohibit a student from possessing or
31 using a personal electronic communication device, if:
